The paper deals with the complexity of computing determinants and counting various types of tours in graphs of bounded tree-width. This is a topic in graph theory and algorithms, which is likely to fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves some linear algebraic techniques, which could place it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with counting problems, which could also place it under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
